    "What this shows: anchoring a link with raw addresses, not only section ids.",
    "First link: from and to both use exactly two hex strings [\"0xSTART\", \"0xEND\"].",
    "That range is chosen to cover Block 3 and Block 4 on purpose — it proves the",
    "band follows those literal addresses across an internal section boundary, not",
    "just one section box.",
    "Second link: from uses a single section id (block_3); to still uses a hex pair.",
    "That shows you can mix id-based and hex-based anchors in one link.",
    "Names are neutral placeholders, not a real chip map."
